<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n50082b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n50" href="#n50082b">N50 (VI.B.37)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n50all.htm#n50082b"> 82(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> whitechrist</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">It was not till the time that the Danes and Norwegians began to invade the countries of the west, and to make great conquests there, and consequently not till the ninth century, that we find the oldest traces of the Danes, or rather perhaps the Danish-Norwegian Vikings, having fought under one flag; which was not, like the earlier ones, that of a single chief, but rather an established national ensign. We must remember that they were heathens, making war upon a Christian land, and fighting for Odin and Thor against <mark>White* Christ</mark>. <small> J.J.A. Worsaae, <a name="JJAW2" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#JJAW2"><cite title="source">An Account of the Danes and Norwegians in England, Scotland and Ireland</cite></a> (1852) 56</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: White, an epithet applied by the Northmen to our Saviour. </mm> </dd></dl>
